calm- partly cloudy   26 feet deep   GPS N45 56.074  W088 35.619 (20 foot variance)
Partly Cloudy + Hazy.  Slightly Windy with No Chop.  At Least 3 Loons.
Sunny breezy. Bottom at 23.4 feet.  Sunny breezy. Bottom at 23.4 feet.
Sunny 22.7 ft.  Calm.  Lake very shallow- lots of new weed growth along shore.
Assisted by Mick Mlinar.  Clear sky.  Observed 3 loons. Assisted by Mick Mlinar.  Clear sky.  Observed 3 loons.
Sunny 20.0 ft.  Calm.  Lake very shallow- lots of new weed growth along shore.
Sunny and breezy. Very windy for three days prior to taking water sample.

column1: 2 loons spotted- their nest was raided by predators.

column2: Sunny and calm. Lake level up 5 inches from rain in June and July.
Sunny- slight breeze. Lake level up 9 inches total. Good rains in august. Still 9 inches below ordinary high water mark.
Sunny and breezy. Lake level continues to rise about another 7 inches to ordinary high water mark.
sunny- calm- 4+ inches of rain prior week
filtered clouds- still pollen in water- very little rain in April/May had lot of windy days
partly cloudy- heavy rain 2 days prior- breezy
sunny and calm- lake level lowest of all year
Slight breeze- sunny- clean- some pollen in water.
Full sun; no breeze; a lot of rain throughout September
sunny- breezy- 73 degrees- lake level 12 inches below June level
Full sun calm 64 degrees. Floating blobs green/blue algae
Cloudy- breeze- 80 degree F air temp- 1" rain at 5AM
Party cloudy- breeze 73 degrees air temp.
